# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PortPane by ShackDesk — Git Ignore Rules
# Project  : https://github.com/Computer-Tsu/shackdesk-portpane
# Author   : Mark McDow (N4TEK) — My Computer Guru LLC
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── .NET build output ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These directories are generated by the compiler and build tools. They are
# large, binary-heavy, and fully reproducible by running "dotnet build". There
# is never a reason to commit them. The .vs/ folder holds Visual Studio's
# per-developer workspace state (breakpoints, window layout) which conflicts
# across machines. *.user and *.suo are per-user IDE preference files.
*.user
*.suo
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates
.vs/
bin/
obj/
publish/
TestResults/
*.nupkg
*.snupkg

# ── Velopack update packages ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Velopack stores built update packages in the Releases/ directory during the
# packaging step. These are distributable artifacts, not source code. They can
# be very large (full application bundles) and are uploaded to GitHub Releases
# or a CDN — not stored in the repository.
Releases/

# ── Log files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Runtime log files generated by Serilog. They are created at runtime in the
# user's AppData or beside the exe (portable mode). Log files may contain
# system information (device names, error details) and are not appropriate for
# a public repository. Attach them to bug reports manually when needed.
*.log
Logs/

# ── User settings and personal configuration ──────────────────────────────────
# Settings files that are generated per-developer or per-machine. These should
# never be committed because they contain personal paths, credentials, or
# machine-specific configuration that would conflict with other contributors.
*.rsuser
appsettings.Development.json
launchSettings.json

# ── Operating system files ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Files created automatically by macOS (.DS_Store), Windows (Thumbs.db,
# desktop.ini), and other OS features. These are meaningless to other platforms
# and clutter the repository.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ── JetBrains Rider ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Rider stores its workspace state in .idea/. Per-developer settings files
# (*.DotSettings.user) contain personal preferences like code style overrides
# that should not override the shared .editorconfig.
.idea/
*.DotSettings.user

# ── VS Code ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VS Code's .vscode/ folder contains editor-specific settings, launch configs,
# and extension recommendations. If shared settings are needed for the project,
# they should be committed explicitly (e.g. .vscode/extensions.json). The
# folder is excluded by default because it frequently contains personal configs.
.vscode/

# ── Icon and image source files ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Source files for the application icon (Photoshop .psd, Illustrator .ai, GIMP
# .xcf) are excluded because they are large binary files that change rarely and
# are not needed to build the application. Only the compiled .ico file is
# committed. Vector source files can be shared via a separate channel if needed.
*.psd
*.ai
*.xcf

# ── SECRETS AND PRIVATE KEYS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# !! WARNING: NEVER COMMIT PRIVATE KEYS, CERTIFICATES, OR SECRETS !!
# The RSA private key used to sign license keys and update manifests must NEVER
# be stored in this repository, even in a private branch. If a private key is
# accidentally committed, rotate it immediately — treat it as compromised.
# Only the PUBLIC key (keys/portpane-public.pem) belongs in the repository.
keys/portpane-private.pem
keys/*.p12
keys/*.pfx
*.p12
*.pfx
*.pem
!keys/portpane-public.pem

# ── AI assistant working files ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Session context and configuration files generated by AI coding tools.
# Not source code — must never be committed.
CLAUDE.md
.claude/
.copilot/
.cursor/
